Document Checklist: All Original When you apply for your Student visa you must provide:
1. ﻿﻿a current passport or other valid travel documentation
2. ﻿﻿a Confirmation of Acceptance for Studies (CAS) from your course provide
3. ﻿﻿proof you have enough money to support yourself and pay for your course - this will vary depending on your circumstances
4. ﻿﻿Academic Documents from 10th till Highest qualification
5. ﻿﻿Work Experience Documents
6. ﻿﻿English Language proficiency
7. ﻿﻿a valid ATAS certificate if your course and nationality require it
8. ﻿﻿proof of parental or other legal guardian consent if you're under 18
9. ﻿﻿proof of your relationship to your parent or guardian if you're under 18 through Birth Certificate
10. ﻿﻿your tuberculosis test results via Approved Test Clinics
11. ﻿﻿written consent for your application from your financial sponsor if you've received sponsorship for your course fees and living costs in the last 12 months

9. ﻿﻿proof of your relationship to your parent or guardian if you're under 18 through Birth Certificate
